Well another fear raid another cr, seems like this is becoming a bogey zone for us atm.<br>
<br>
Was asphixias raid and thanks to him for setting it up and getting groups organised etc, I said i'd help on tactics so the 5 hours cr comes on to my shoulders.<br>
<br>
Kk start at the beginning, we had some no shows but in the main everyone turned up - Asp got some good replacements in 60 chanter, 4th cleric, 55 tank but we were waiting a while to group and it was an hour before we were ready to break.<br>
<br>
Not much could be done about this as I only got on at the start time, but as always we need to have a break team an hour earlier to save the hanging around.<br>
<br>
Fdrs went in peaceably and then the strong fight and evac team went in, thats when things went wrong! the fight teams tanks hung at the portal too long, got agro, fought at the portal, got more agro, died and then the mobs came for us.<br>
<br>
With no assist tanks at the west camp, people were confused and dissorientated and we suffered some bad loses.<br>
<br>
This is effectively what stuffed us up, we took down no mobs on that first fight and instead had stirred up a lot of wanderers making regular circuits of the portal.<br>
<br>
2nd break team got ready and zoned just as wanderers mobbed the portal, bad luck really but in hindsight evac should have been called as soon as agro was gained. While its common to stand and die in fear when you get attacked, if your cleric is the one standing and dying your group is going straight to hell anyway.<br>
<br>
With the first and second break groups ganked we were struggling, we'd lost the bulk of our best people without killing any mobs. After that we tried getting inventive, 3 chanters to keep mobs clear for rez stick - failed and more dead. The old fashioned break tactic with the remaining groups charging camp site while cleric got camped - failed and more dead.<br>
<br>
After this we were always going to need outside help to break, we got a couple of people in and tried various break and evac tactics but they failed too, in the end Stoic came and broke it for us, then rode off on their silver horses.<br>
<br>
Thanks to Kaiser and all of Stoic, they were quick, friendly and didn't chuckle once <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
After we rezzed everyone, 5 hours had passed and a lot of people had no exp rez corpses, some left and some stayed.<br>
<br>
For the people who stayed it was actually a fun sort of raid, we knew time was limited and saw shissar was up for chanter epic and went for it.<br>
<br>
We cleared north pretty well and got some armor, then pulled temple very well and got more armor, got the shissar and grats to Sihdarta on a difficult peice of his epic.<br>
<br>
The good points, we got chanter epic peice, we got some upgrades for a few people, we ended up turning a lousy raid around and at least got something out of it. Attitude as always was good, some people were asking more about rezzes than others but after 5 hours I know I would be too, didn't hear many people bitch and complain and thats always a strong point of ours.<br>
<br>
Bad points, people need to listen, looking back the move to west camp was explained clearly at least twice and at least 2 of the people in first break group were seasoned vets of fear, if we have people new to a zone in important positions on a raid we're gonna have to lead em by the nose in the future.<br>
<br>
Only way I see of avoiding a repeat of this is checking with everyone that they know exactly what they have to do, have higher levels on the break in to allow for mistakes and evac at first sign of trouble if your group gets hit before you make the camp.<br>
<br>
Asp is gonna post another one for a few weeks time and we'll take special care and attention next time to avoid anything like this happening again.<br>
<br>
All for the want of a Nail.......<br>
