<br>
The main reason I think we failed is we moved to quickly.  This is the reason pick-up Fear raids or casual attempts on Fear are rarely successful.  We had a very late start, and the no-shows left us alittle weak in some class areas.  I contacted a few guildies and almost as soon as everyone new to the raid arrived we made ready to begin the break.  Eldark did an excellent job of &quot;taking the reigns&quot; (no offence to you, Asphyxia, but Eldark had experience with Fear raid leading and was a natural leading force, I am glad you let him take charge).  He communicated very clearly what the plan was, and what people were to do.<br>
<br>
The disaster that resulted was a combination of bad luck, inexperienced raiders, and more bad luck.  We had alot of unnecessary chatter in the raid channel, and I am certain this led to the miscommunication which made things go wrong.<br>
<br>
Just to point out what I consider to be a successful strategy in breaking Fear, and by no means do I take credit for it's genius - <br>
<br>
- Feign Death capable characters zone in together and head to the left of zone - in, down the hill and to the ledge where camp is usually initially set up.  They zone in, get there, Feign dead, and quit out.  They wait a second for mobs to disburse, log back in, re-FD if necessary, and report camp status to the break group(s)<br>
<br>
- The break groups are fully buffed and ready with at least one Evacuation casting party member, if not two.  It is best IMO to have TWO break groups, as they can be a more potent force, but often a single group is used as it is more manageable.<br>
<br>
- Once the break groups zone in they head straight down to the camp.  They try desperately NOT to aggro mobs along the way, but so long as the mobs brought to camp are manageable by the enchanters so be it.  Players hit by a scarling and sent to whoknowswhere are expected to die where they stand (after being 'gated' by the scarling proc) as opposed to training a horde of mobs back to the group, causing a wipeout.<br>
<br>
- Once at the camp, enchanters mez all mobs they can, and the FD-ers join them in killing as many mobs as possible before the cleric or enchanter run out of mana.  The Evacuation casters should be continually casting and then cancelling their evacuation spells if the situation is difficult.  At first indication that things may turn bad, they should let the spell go off and rescue their group.  FD-ers then FD and quit to clear aggro.   Rinse and repeat until the zone in area is clear, and the remainding members of the raid can zone in and normal groups be established.<br>
<br>
This is a tried and true strategy.  When we have been rescued by other guilds they usually only do it with two well equipped groups.  Their tanks know how to TAUNT mobs off enchanters and healers WITHOUT attacking, their tanks know how to assist when the MT hails the target mob to kill.  They work as a team to clear mobs effectively, and if they need to die to prevent training the group, they die.<br>
<br>
There is a great strategy for breaking (and clearing) Fear with Area-of-Effect spells and I would LOVE to try this out, but I don't think that is even a viable option if we cannot get the old fashioned, reliable strategy down flawlessly.<br>
<br>
Fear is difficult.  Stoic members came right out and told me that there is nothing to be embarassed about a failed breaking of the plane, it can be a real bear sometimes.<br>
<br>
P.S. When the raid leader says someone is giving the word on when to zone in, or delegates responsibility to someone in a group - EVERYONE is to respect this, including 'usual' Federation raidleaders.  If we don't follow the plan as it is laid out things are bound to go awry and get ugly.<br>
<br>
P.P.S. I am very glad we continued on after the almost comically dreadful beginning.  I ended up having a great time and am glad we turned it around and showed our true colors kicking Fear butt.  Congratulations to everyone receiving loot, and THANK YOU AGAIN VERY MUCH Stoic for being our Guardian Angels and saving the day, I hope we can return the favor someday  /snicker  /bonk     <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=70.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=70.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.threadControl?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=70.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.unsubscribeUn